<subSubSection pageNumber="766" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="766">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="766">Note:</emphasis>
Although Stearn (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="766">
Introd. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
Sp. Pl.
</emphasis>
(Ray Soc. ed.): 127. 1957) says this is &quot;to be typified by [a] specimen
<normalizedToken originalValue="…">...</normalizedToken>
from Gmelin in the Linnaean herbarium&quot;, it is unclear which collection was intended. Both 655.46 and 655.47 (LINN) carry 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“22”">&quot;22&quot;</normalizedToken>
(the number of this species account in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="766">
<volumeTitle>Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
), but neither is indicated directly as coming from Gmelin, and the collections are not clearly part of a single gathering. The name, which is currently untypified, is in use for an Asiatic taxon (see 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Soják">Sojak</normalizedToken>
in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="766">Preslia</emphasis>
65: 129. 1993) in a taxonomically complex group of species.
</paragraph>
